Reasoning: The paper deals with planning problems in complex systems with mixed discrete and continuous state and action spaces, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep neural network models for state transitions and the development of planning methods based on these models also falls under these categories. The paper also discusses the application of these methods in control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the optimization techniques used in the paper may also be relevant to the field of data science (cs.DS).
